{"word":"κατάσκιος","slug":"κατάσκιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατάσκιος</b></el> <el>(κατά-σκιος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκιά'><el>σκιά</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>shaded</i> or <i>covered with</i> something, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>overshadowing</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}